723340f-b.text:

723341f-a.title: Manhattan: South Street - Rutgers Slip
723341f-a.text:
South Street, west from (No, 252) but not including Rutgers Slip,
showing in the foreground a portion of the Manhattan Bridge. lIn the distance
appears the Brooklyn Bridge. Silhouetted across the skyline, are;,the
Farmer's Loan and Trust Co.; the 60 Wall Street Tower; the Bank of the
Manhattan Co.; the Singer (with dome), and the Woolworth Buildings.
March 22, i937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, slightly westward. The intersection shown in the fore-
ground is Pike Slip. This Street parallels the East River of which,
several Piers are seen on the left.
March 22, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
